<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                        <head>EXHIBIT B.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Office
                                        of the Collector of Customs.<lb/>Port of San Francisco,
                                        Cal.</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-29"><hi rend="italic">March 29,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I hereby certify that the records of this office show that the American
                            schooner <hi rend="italic">J. H. Lewis</hi>, A. McLean, master, of 78
                            tons, cleared at this port for a hunting and fishing voyage on the 7th
                            day of March, 1891.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">N. S. Farley</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Deputy Collector of
                            Customs.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>[<hi rend="smallcaps">stamp.</hi>]</p>
                            <p>Fee, 20 cents, paid.</p>
                            <closer><dateline rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cashier’s
                                        Office, Custom-House</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San Francisco</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-29"><hi rend="italic">March 29, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></closer>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>